<br>
For the most part, server patches happen at 8pm (1am PST) or 10pm (3am PST) which means the servers come back up ready for US play times and all the guilds in the Asian zone (inc Aust/NZ) have left is whatever scraps the US folks couldn't take down before their raiders started sleeping at the console.<br>
<br>
On one or two recent lucky occasions the server has bounced during our work day and come up just before we're ready to start playing so we've had the luxury of a larger number of named mobs up (Velk, Vindi etc).<br>
<br>
I can't speak for the Euroguilds but they'll be somewhere in the middle. Depleted somewhat by the Aust/Asian guilds play but also some pops starting to happen again.<br>
<br>
Ooger's reasoning remains valid though. On many other servers the FCFS/FFA is much more brutal and some of the big guild monopolise the spawns. This random element helps to spread it out a little so that (as VI said in the patch news) it'll be fairer to all timezones. Ooger did say 'on other servers' but I think the logistics of server patches, pop times and speed of mobilisation would apply equally across all servers.<br>
<br>
